They ask how my daughter got into reading. I just pick up a book, and she follows. It made me realize, she picks up everything. The frustrations, sure. But also the little acts of care – like making sure her mother feels cherished with @orimiiskincare, or getting up for her water. Our kids see the full picture. And knowing that is the ultimate nudge to always do better. It’s not a perfect performance, but a consistent pattern of love.❤️

Forgetting toys, missing story time... maybe I’m a 5/10 dad on the small things. 😅
But for the big things, like securing their future, it’s always a 10/10.
